text: Mr Anderson, I am the cashier that waited on your wife that morning. First of all, I need you to understand I wasn’t ignoring her. You also forgot to mention that your wife was trying to shut you up when you came in yelling and cursing at me. You also forgot to mention when you were cursing at me all I said to you was sir please leave the store. Not that it’s your business but I chose 3rd shift. My customers are my number one priority. I take my job very serious when it comes to my customers. I don’t like  that you’re unhappy,but I also know everyone can’t be pleased. I know you said your wife was disabled... maybe you should try getting out for her next time if 1 minute is too much time for her to be up.  You sure were able to get out to cuss me out. I don’t like that you’re unhappy with me, but I’ve done nothing wrong. Don’t know what else to say. Have a great day and “Take it easy”.

She says that she needs to have them INCASE someone else wants to purchase them.   Tell me why would you refuse to sale any items in a store that is there to be sold in the first place. We have six tobacco users in my home. And three of the members are guys so they dip and smoke. I promise you that you may not miss one sale but the couple of hundreds of dollars we spend a week is gone. I was understanding the many times I have gone in and they didn’t have enough there. But I asked them to please order so many cans for my hubby and we would buy them every other week. He is a OTR driver and preferred to give his money to the town we live in

He brought my wallet with him to college in Boston and kept it safe till last month then texted me when he was back home in Alabama and he mailed it to me. I just got it. Not one thing is missing or out of place. I am sooo super thankful for Ali. The gas station is okay too but it's the people that matter most to me. I really wish I could give this place 10 stars. Thank you! 😀😀😀😀😀😀

name: M J
text:
I highly recommend avoiding this particular Shell location at 2890 Acton Road based on my recent experience with them.

On what will most definitely be my final visit, I selected the 87 grade gas (as I've done every time I've purchased gas over the last 25 years), and proceeded to fill my tank up.

Once my tank was full, I glanced up and noticed a total amount that caught me off guard. I was later reviewing my receipt, and noticed that the pump had somehow charged me for the premium gas that was positioned on the opposite side of the pump (and was exactly $1 more per gallon).

I immediately drove back to this gas station to share my experience with the attendant. In the end, he told me there was nothing he could do about it.

The total cost difference between the grade of gas I chose and what I was charged for came out to around $14.50 for a single fill-up. Needless to say, that isn't sitting well with me, and I'd like to issue a warning to others with hope that it prevents someone else from having a similar terrible experience with this business.

I filled up the car, then realised that the little service dog of my mom needed a drink. I walked in with the doggie under my arm, excused myself, and asked for some water for the doggie. The unsmiling and hostile woman behind the counter said  The sink! and did not bother to even point to it. I said thank you, looked around,found the sink, and reached for an empty paper cup. At this point the woman  shouted angrily You can't have that! And glared at me hatefully. I was shocked. I had never been treated like this, especially in the South. I do have a foreign accent. I do understand rules - she could have smiled and told me sorry, I cannot spare you a cup though you just spent 40 dollars on had here. Then I would have smiled too and bought some bottled water.      This woman is  a disgrace to your business. We will never stop by again. For your reference, this was around
4  pm  on Thursday April 6.

What a way to start a long weekend. I really do believe that nasty people better work in nonservice jobs. I am in a service job myself. Everything matters. Kindness and courtesy go along way. Alas, ugliness also does.

resp.text:
Hi Tony,

Retail gas prices are a reflection of the current function of supply and demand and are ultimately set by the individual retail sites, which are independently owned and operated. Many factors contribute to gas prices, which the Energy Information Administration discusses at the following page: http://www.eia.gov/energyexplained/index.cfm?page=gasoline_factors_affecting_prices

We are sorry to hear about your experience with the owners. We will pass this along to the Consumer Relations team, who will notify the owner of your experience.

Thanks,
BP

I noticed I was out of gas so I pulled in.  I then realized that I had left my billfold and I also did not have any spare cash in my console.  I was parked in front of gas pump at 3am.  I then was told by Jessica an employee that I couldnt be blocking her pumps and costing them business I told her what was going on and asked would it be ok to pull in a parking space.  She said u have been since I came on. I responded I know I dont want to go far cause I will run out I am trying to call a friend.  Officer Bivens said I was fine.
Then 3 hours later the Pepsi man was trying to get in to the store and his load fell over. I then helped him pick it all up and he got in the door.  Later on he came out and asked if I was out of gas or could he help.  He put in 10.00 for me.  Jason is his name and I appreciate that.   I had then already contacted my brother who was on the way also.   But the treatment I received from this employee really hurts the kind spirit of mankind.  Instead of asking what was gojng on and listening to what I was doing she immediately was on the defensive with you got to move. You are blocking my gas pumps costing me business.  It was 3 am.  I was the only one out there with my dog.  On the phone trying to get some money.   I only lived 20 miles away but I was on empty and I will always check before I leave the house and I will always have cash in the car.  I will never stop agajn at this station I will just run out of gas.

name: Paul M
text:
Never EVER rent a moving truck from this location.  Not sure why Budget allows these people to use it's name, but their customer service is awful.  They did not put the hand dolly in the truck for me when I rented a truck from there.  I live about 25 miles away from there, and so to drive the Budget truck back there for the dolly, it used up over five gallons of fuel round trip.  That's over $20 worth of fuel I have to put back into the truck now because it has to be full when you turn it in.  They refused to fill the truck back up even though I had to use the gas because of their mistake.

Budget has a limit of 212 miles of use when you rent a truck, and I had to use 50 of those miles going back for the dolly they forgot.  I will now have to pay a penalty for going over my miles when I turn the truck in.  They refused bring me the dolly or even meet me closer to my home with the dolly even though it was their mistake.  The employee I was working with told me repeatedly it wasn't her problem and she didn't care (I recorded her saying it on my iPhone).  And when I asked to speak to the owner, he said he wouldn't help me because I'm moving far away and I guess I won't be around to use Buddy's Service Center anymore.  Said it wouldn't benefit him financially to make the gas in the truck right.  And when I asked if happy customers benefit him financially he just shrugged his shoulders and said he didn't care.

The employee then went on to shove my paperwork into my stomach where I was leaning against the counter and refused to answer any more questions.  The owner then said the employee would not be punished for her actions.

Do yourself a favor and use Uhaul or Ryder or anyone else.  Budget Customer Service would not help with the gas either.  They said I used the gas and didn't care that I only had to use it because of their mistake they made.

Moving is stressful enough already.  Do yourself a favor and don't add to that stress by using Budget and definitely don't add to it by using Buddy's Service Center.  Buddy is apparently an uncaring jerk.

text:
Update: regional manager personally called me and validated my concerns. Says a fix is coming, admitted to network issues and apologized for staff and network issues. Taking a wait and see approach. And adding back some stars.

About one out of every three times I come in to use my MapcoExpress discount the gas pump times out, causing me to change pumps and lose my reward discount. Tonight I stood there for over 10 minutes waiting, which is what the screen said to do. I pressed the call attendant button many, many times, to no avail. I finally went inside, and there was no one in there. Looked around and finally was given the international sign for wait a minute from one of the three employees in the back. I waited and was again told it wasn't their fault and there is nothing they can do, which I already knew. You have a telecom issue and never fix it. I don't care if it is a corporate office issue, it affects me, my time, my mood, and my price of gas. I drive by 15 stations to come to your station and yet it's not your problem. I'm aware it is my problem, businesses with customer focused attitudes make my problem their problem. Maybe you could start there...

text: Today around 1pm I visited GASBOY CALERA.1st I'll say this is an excellently maintained station that I now know is locally owned and independently operated. That is 👍 great! With that being said my 1st experience at GASBOY CALERA  was less than spectacular. I came in looking for a restroom, looked on the door saw the male/female sign and no letter indicating I couldn't use it. I did my business, cleaned up after myself and went to the counter to make a purchase. I politely asked the clerk how she was doing. I don't know her name, maybe she was the owner. She gave me no reply and had the most disgruntled look on her face. As I am paying, I asked asked her why she seemed upset. She angrily said, "HOW ABOUT NEXT TIME YOU DICIDE TO "BLOW UP" SOMEONE'S TOILET YOU ASK!". To which I calmly replied, "You should put a sign on the door letting customers know to ask". As I'm leaving she said with agrivation, "YOU SHOULD ASK!" Maybe I was wrong for not asking, but I don't think I deserved the level of disrespect this woman gave me. If she is the owner of this store, she should seriously rethink her attitude and how she treats her "paying customers". If she is an employee of the store, the owner should reconsider keeping her employed. Its not a good look for a proudly locally owned and independently operated GASBOY Citgo of Calera.

While standing in line for which seemed like forever, and with my aunt standing outside in below freezing weather waiting to pump she asks one of the attendents walking inside "hey can yall turn the pump on?" To which the girl very rudely responds "uh no! Not til you pay!" Well I, still standing in line, speak up and say "well I'm in line to pay now, I wanna fill my car up" an she tells me "yea an as soon as you pay we'll turn the pump on" and someone who I'm guessing was the attendents friend pops off an says "yea they don't turn the pump on until you pay because that's how they get burned" I just say "okay whatever, obviously I'm not going anywhere if I'm standing inside" so I pay for my gas an go back outside I'm telling my aunt what took so long when the girl (friend) comes out an says "you know what? There's more gas stations around here in a one mile radius you ho!" An jumps in her car an took off

♿ Wheelchair accessible entrance, bathroom,  & parking.

name: LiLnUgGeT666
text:
I will never visit this location again. The employee that was working tonight/morning was one of the most rude people I've ever encountered. I greeted him with "Good morning, how are you sir?". He responded with only a cold stair as if I wasn't allowed or supposed to be there.

I had an arm full of stuff to purchase and he wasn't at a register when I approached so I unknowingly sat the items at the wrong one. When he eventually sauntered over instead of helping me move the items to the correct one, he just pointed and approached it and staired at me while I moved everything. I didn't mind having to move my stuff but, in my eyes, proper customer service would dictate the employee assist in moving everything because I had no idea I was at the incorrect register when I sat the things down. He also was not wearing a mask, even though there is a sign on the doors saying "masks required inside this facility".

Anyway, maybe I'm just being petty, but it just irked me the wrong way, him with his superior attitude and all. In the grand scheme of things im sure my contributions won't be missed, but treating people in the manner he did me will eventually lead to more people never returning. Management of this facility should probably look for some workers with at least a small amount of pride in their job. I get its only a fuel station attendant job but all jobs, especially ones dealing with the public, should show a little pride in their work and make the customer feel welcome.

Out of know where, a small petite female yelled from the register saying be quiete! She kept yelling at me in front of customers. I preceded  to the register to pay for my items while the person kept yelling at me.. I told the cashier let me pay for my items because I have to go to work. text: I have been a 30 year customer but had a terrible experience today and will not go back.  The cashier was incredibly rude to me. I paid extra for love bug removal. If came within an inch of being hit. One of the workers finally got into my car and pulled back into the parking lot. I went back to the young lady at the desk and asked for the manager. The manager came out asked what was going on and I explained to her what happened. She told me no there is an hump that stops the vehicles. So, I explained to her again what happened. She looked at me and said I'll talk to the crew. With no apology or anything she walked outside and I never saw her again. My vehicle was finally done. Very  mediocre job of drying and wiping everything down.  Employee raises his hand for me to come out there. He asked how I was, I explained not good cause my car rolled into the middle of the street. He said " WE HAD CAUD IT DO".  All I could do is shake my head and leave.  If you use this car wash pray someone gets in your vehicle before it rolls into the street. Good Luck.

name: Nitro Motors Wheel Repair
text: I would give ZERO stars if it was possible. Horrible customer service, rude and in my entire professional career in the automotive industry pumping fuel 5-6 times a day, I have never been treated like dirt or degraded in such a humiliating way.  I prepaid for my fuel among other things and in my haste drove away only to realize I did not pump fuel.  I immediately went back, however the pump was either reset or another customer took advantage of the free fuel.  I went back in to ask for assistance, hoping when meters were read and fuel was out of balance, or someone had reported the situation.  A shorter, middle-aged man with a thick accent would not allow me to ask a question, finish my sentence, much less explain the situation.  I was not looking for free fuel - simply there is nothing we can do. From the moment I spoke, he screamed, yelled, repeatedly exclaimed, "it's not my fault, it's not my fault!" and would not allow me to continue.  He belittled me and spoke down to me as though I was trash, with multiple customers waiting in line with their jaws dropped in disbelief.  I simple gave up, gave him $10.00 to prepay for fuel (again). But he continued his tyrant and I had to ask several times for my receipt before he finally handed it to me.  At that point, I wanted my receipt, my new purchase and to leave.  If this gentleman is the manager or owner, I certainly have lost respect for him and absolutely refuse to visit Exxon in Saginaw, AL. A little common courtesy goes a long way.  As I stated, I wanted nothing for free and someone else benefited from my loss, fine, they are better for it, but to be treated as I was, while spending money at his store is a true testament to the type of business he runs.  Horrific.

name: James Breaux
text:
I can't say enough how kind and sweet the owner of this store is!!!
After driving for 30+ miles in the pouring rain and gas tank on E, I pulled into the parking lot of Fields Grocery.  There were no cars in the parking lot, gas pumps looked ancient, and a closed sign was taped to the front door. I assumed the place was no longer in business. Not only that, but I had no cell service to even call AAA to bring gas. My family and I were essentially stranded.
It must have been our lucky day because the owner of Fields Grocery & Gas was kind enough to leave her house during the rain storm and open the store for us so we could purchase gas. Needless to say, the pumps were still operational!
If you're traveling down HWY69 make sure to stop here. You'll get a great history lesson on the area and of the store. You'll also get to meet the owner who convinced me there are still kind people in this world.

Tonight for dinner: fried fish fillets, turnip greens, mashed potatoes, regular cornbread, and a piece of birthday sprinkle vanilla cake with lemon frosting for dessert. Finish it off with a cup of sweet tea. ❤ (Obviously I like their fried fish fillets.)

Also, they have since remodeled the restrooms and have added showers for $10.00 each. Dont listen to the folks who are fussin' in the comment section here. Come on in and try out Cafe 30, great truck parking (if you get in at a decent time) and friendly folks inside. 👍🏻👍🏻

Will stop here again.

name: BOGUS Blank
text: Women behind counter said nothing at all.when I go to a normal place of business I am usually greeted with hello may I help you.not here made me feel like I did something wrong or maybe my long hair out of place for the southern folks.when I did get my food of which I ordered to go I had to ask for a bag.oh bathroom stalls are falling apart and no paper towels in bathroom how is a trucker going to wash their face and dry it?oh I know stick your head in the blow dryer! Other than all that it's a place to park and go to the restroom as long as you don't expect any privacy when you sit on the toilet.

name: Ana Shomaker
text:
This place was disgusting, the guy who runs it is trash too. I told him the restrooms were beyond filthy and he told me that it was only him there and that he has 1 person come clean it at night, I told him they could do a better job because it doesn’t look like anything has been wiped down swept or mopped or weeks.
It’s prolly got parasites all over the place.

It’s even more disappointing that when I told the man he didn’t even apologize he just argued with me about it.
Also across the board the gas has been anywhere from 2.30 to 2.50 and his gas was way over priced at 2.75.
Pretty sure he was selling cigarettes to underage kids as well.

text: If I could give 0 stars I would. I am a woman truck driver and this bathroom was absolutely unacceptable, I've been through my fair share of truck stop bathrooms and this was by far the worst! One toilet seat wasn't even on the toilet and the other toilet was stuffed with toilet paper to the point where I was scared to flush it to try to use the bathroom. I don't understand how so many women work here and that bathroom is not decent, you have to use that bathroom all day! Living in a truck these bathrooms are my only options and I've never been so pissed, sad sad excuse for a truck stop! If you have a wife or you are a woman truck driver do yourself a favor and pass this exit, for your own health. I'm very upset about having to stop here for the night.

name: Jenna Leigh's Beauty Slam
text: This little store epitomizes "small town corner store". Once upon a time, it really WAS the only gas station or convenience store for many miles. Over the last two decades, Saraland has seen some incredible growth, and Kali-Oka Road is certainly not exempt from that. Yet the Country Corner is still there; not too far away now ARE enormous 10, 20 pump gas stations with built-in restaurants and a ton of amenities. Yet the Country Corner continues to thrive for several reasons: loyalty. There are teenagers pumping gas there who's grandparents pumped their gas there. Convenience. Even though there are the massive gas stations right around the corner, the CC is smack dab in the middle of Kali-Oka. And the folks who work there are ALWAYS beyond nice. The CC is almost like a "throwback" to old corner stores.

name: Mike Mason
text:
Hands down, the absolute BEST Bar-B-q not only in town but in St. Clair county. They are proud of it but it's not reflected in their prices.
Teeth are not required for any of their quality, well prepared meats. Rib meat literally falls off the bone. So tender you can almost eat the bones themselves. You choose the sauce you prefer and their menu is large. They offer family meals as well as party size orders. There is decent barbq nearby in town but none of it even comes close to this store's fine Q.
Today i was served a HUGE T-bone steak with potato and side salad for $11.99.
Your simply not gonna beat that.
And if your in the mood for a simple bbq sammich then they have a sammich, bag-o-chips and 20 oz. drink deal. Trust me when I tell you. It's worth it. Stay away from "gas station sushi" but this bbq is worth a 50 mile drive and thats the honest truth.
Enjoy.

name: Jessica Heyer
text:
BEWARE!!  CARD SKIMMER ON CREDIT CARD MACHINE AT THE REGISTER INSIDE THE STORE.
When I used my debit card at this store on July 17, 2018, I was required to enter my pin # two times- once at the beginning of the transaction and again at the end of the transaction. I Asked the cashier why I was required to enter my pin twice and she quickly looked away nervously and didn't respond. I then turned the machine and looked closely at the side where cards are swiped. The machine appeared to have an overlay that had been mounted to the credit card machine. When I looked up, the cashier looked away quickly and would not make eye contact.

The following day, July 18, I began to see fraudulent charges posting to my bank account. I reported the charges to regions and was told by the bank manager that it appeared that someone had cloned my debit card. Regions is opening an investigation into the fraud.

TO THE OWNER OF THIS STORE-
YOUR EMPLOYEE (white female with brown hair, approx late 30s to 40s) that was working the register on July 17, 2018 around 1pm is a thief!!
If she stole from me, she'll steal from you and the rest of your customers!!

resp.text:
Thank you Erin for your review.  I am looking into this situation and please know that I take this issue  very serious.  I would love to speak to you to acquire more details . Country Convenience has never had this happen before.
Thank You   Patti Middleton  251-964-5674  or 251-747-7581

text: This place was amazing! I had to use the restroom very badly and this place seems like it's in the middle of no where. I entered the store and was shocked! The store was warm, smelled "homey", the staff very friendly. The bathrooms both male and female were spotless clean! The stuff they had there was so unique and interesting! I would definitely make this a routine stopping point if coming through this way again!

name: John O'Dell
text:
We stopped mainly to use the restroom but upon entering, we were so amazed by the merchandise, the cleanliness of the store and the sparkling restrooms, we had to grab something to eat at the adjacent restaurant.
The burger and onion rings that we ordered were beyond heaven, beautifully cooked and prepared.
The burger was made of one pound of beef and cooked to perfection with just the right amount of condiments and pickles.
My wife and I shared a single burger cut in half and almost couldn’t finish it.
The onion rings were sweet and fried in the perfect batter and were filled with flavor like they should be.
Do not pass up an opportunity to stop by and meet the friendliest people in Alabama as well as the cleanest restrooms for three states.
But most of all....DO NOT pass up the chance to eat some of the best food in the south.

text: I started using this gas station within the last 2 years. In the past I never really cared for the location tho now I'm not sure why. I rarely go elsewhere.  Their icee's are fire,  they carry Tastycake powdered donuts, nice selection of wine- I'm kinda assuming this.  I know nothing about wine but they have a bunch of different ones so I figured the possibility was high. The employees are super nice. One lady (who loves Alabama football) did me an absolute solid. "I" accidently left my 4yo's cup in the store while she was working. I had no idea.  Searched everywhere (I thought) for 2 days.  We have other cups, too many actually but he prefers the one abandoned. Can't blame him,  I have my own cup that no others can live up to. I get it. We went back to the store on day 2. While checking out she says "oh yeah" or something of the sort. She walks away, comes back with cup while telling me I'd left it. Glad she cleared that up cause home invasion had popped in my mind. It is a Cars cup after all. I apologize to Trussville PD explaining false alarm and hang up. That's a joke, they have me blocked. Anyway, I thank her a bunch, tell her how happy I am to have it, 4yo says "thank you" cause he should. I'll allow note taking just this once. We leave, I hear something fall off car. I stop and back up only to hear a crunch. It's pretty loud. Reluctantly I step out of the vehicle and start laughing hoping to lighten the blow. I ran over my chips. Didn't see that coming did you. Deuces.

text: This used to be a pretty decent fuel station with a pretty good deli. But since it has changed owners and turned into some kind of hybrid circle k, BP, whatever it is, this place has just gotten rundown and just plain gross. The deli, the actual store, the restrooms, everything. At 6:30 A.M., the coffee bar was out of everything but decaf, the creamer machines are out of service, and the whole thing looked like kindergartners had played in it! If this is in fact a Circle K, it is one of the sorriest ones I have ever been in. If you can just hold it for one more exit, I would highly recommend passing this place on by.

name: Thomas Earp
text: Prepaid for $20 on diesel in an F250 while helping our daughter move and they held $300 for about a week. The bank shut off our card because of suspected fraudulent activity immediately. Called to find out what happened, everyone was very rude and less than helpful. We had to wait for new cards to be mailed out. We haven't been back since, there are plenty of much better choices in the area, and we have told all of our friends to be very cautious. Terrible, terrible  choice to do business here. It was much better prior to changing from BP. I just feel sorry for people traveling that don't know better.

resp.text: Hi Thomas, we are sorry about your recent experience. We have passed on your message to our local management team. Please feel free to contact us via email https:// www.circlek.com/contact-form for further assistance.

text: Wasn't open, even though it says 24 hour. Useless.

name: mitchell black
text: I always want a receipt on diesel but don't always print at pump

name: Jennifer Eaton
text: Just a gas station.. nothing spectacular

name: Jennifer Eaton
text: Not Bad at all.

name: Nicholas Swiney
text: I WORK HERE

name: Dale Rowland
text: Very nice people great people to do business with always been nice to me will keep on going there as long as they are in business.

name: Night Owl
text: Awesome food. All home made! Ribs and much more. Pies and cakes!

name: Kimmie Bohannon
text: No one wears a mask here. Even when making food. Plus there food is alway old and terrible. They also close whenever they feel like it

name: Chris PENNINGTON
text: Great place to stop! Good food, fast friendly service, was a nice suprise!

name: Steven ogle
text: Love the pizzas here...and the workers are all ways nice!

name: Thomas Lollar
text: Arrived at 1830 on Sunday.  Already closed.  Hope all is good.

name: NoMore Abuse
text:
Very mean owner he cursed me after I asked if they had premium, which they do not. The food is sold old and they over charge badly. Take my advice..
DO NOT STOP HERE.........

name: Terry L. Catlett
text: This place is the place for all your convenient store needs fair pricing and they are mostly always friendly

name: Misty Catlett
text: I love this store and my family loves Leslie. She's super friendly, works hard and a lot. She also does a lot there. She needs a raise for all her hard work and dedication.

name: Chris PENNINGTON
text: Great place to stop in!! Fast, Clean, and friendly service!!

name: Tina Overton
text: There great getting you in an out the door.

name: Dwayne scott Gosa
text: Everyone is friendly and respectful

name: Terry L. Catlett
text: Leslie, Dede, and Rose are awesome and always makes you feel welcome and at home.

resp.text: Thank you

name: Amanda Whitman
text: They are closed at 10 pm on Saturday night when it says 24 hours on that day.......

name: The Queen of Death
text: Always nice friendly faces no matter what time it is.

name: Matthew Lincoln
text: Very friendly employees and very kind althought sometimes it takes a while for the main guy to understand English havent been disappointed yet and it's the only gas station actually open 24/7 so that's a plus

name: Lynn Pope
text: One of the best burgers ever! The store/ Cafe was very clean and well organized, our food was cooked to order, the fries were fresh  and the staff was very friendly. Lisa was very kind and helpful. We will make the drive again. Thank you for a great experience 💜

resp.text: Thank you Lynn for your review! We hope to see you again soon!

name: Sierra Nave
text: My husband ordered the Blue Hole burger & tater wedges. He said it tasted like a homemade burger. Don't get no better than that. It was only a 1/2 pound of meat, but this burger was huge!

resp.text: Thank you for your review! We do strive for the homemade taste!  Look forward to seeing you again!

name: PR Heinl
text: Good food, a little slow on service, but they were busy. So, I'll give them a pass, the staff was friendly, enjoyed the visit. In response to the reply: I understand, still a great experience. Enjoyed the bacon cheeseburger, it was excellent.

resp.text: So glad you enjoyed your food. Sorry to hear about the service we are short staffed at the moment but doing our best to bring in new help. Hope to see you again soon.

name: Shana Durdin
text: Stopped here for lunch after hiking at Little River NP. We had burgers, bologna sandwiches and BLT’s and everything was so good! Lots of picnic tables outside to hang out and eat!

resp.text: Shana we are so glad you guys choose  to stop and have lunch with us. We do appreciate your feedback we depend on our customers letting us know when we get it right. Please stop by the next time you get a chance. Thanks so very much.

name: Eden Smith
text: My husband and I stopped in for a quick dinner and discovered karaoke night! We were quickly served and it was the best cheeseburger and fries in town. Food was hot fresh and prepared just the way one would want. Bathroom was also squeaky clean and all attendants were courteous and made us feel welcomed! We will definitely return! I just feel like this place needs more recognition!

resp.text: We are so glad you guys had a good experience with us and look forward to serving you again soon.

name: Brenda Bone
text: Awesome food, very friendly staff and I will go back. I had the steak and cheese sandwich with okra.

resp.text: Brenda you are so kind to take time to write us such a great review. Thank you and hope to serve you again soon.

name: Jeffrey Hudson
text: Food was amazing,  Cheese sticks, patti melt for me, and my wife loved her chicken sandwich. Great value and prices are good. Homemade ranch was the perfect finish.

resp.text: Thank you for your review! We appreciate your business and hope to see you again soon!

name: Shannon Marsicano
text: We stopped here after a hike at the waterfall. Staff was all friendly and pleasant to meet! Also BBQ pork sandwiches with slaw from the cafe were on point!

resp.text: Thank you Shannon for your feedback great way for us to know our customers and how we are doing. We hope you will come back soon. Have a great weekend.

name: Richard Hartline
text: Great food and nice people. My wife and I love everything we have ordered. They serve breakfast, lunch, and supper. You can eat from the hot bar or order off the menu. Good portions, too. So far, I've ordered take out, but they have seating for about 30 people. It is also a convenience store and gas station.

name: Luann Chastain
text: Yummy!  Everything is cooked after you order!  Really good bacon burger.  Patty filled the bun and was really flavorful and juicy!  Worth the twisty road to get there.

resp.text: Thank you for your review! We look forward to seeing you again! Have great day!

name: Clark L
text:
We were visiting the Little River Canyon area and stopped by. We were warmly greeted as we came in and also chatted with the folks behind "the grill". I asked what the favorites were on the menu and the prompt reply was "really, everything is good." Well, I can't vouch for everything, because we only tried the breakfast burritos 😊 The good: ample portion and tasty.
The so-so : rather salty and it took QUITE a while to prepare. Now, since we were meandering and not in a hurry, not a problem for us , but, you may want to be aware. Also have some Tshirts, souvenirs and grocery items ( that you pass on the way to a clean bathroom).

name: Todd Milsaps
text:
Granted there's not a lot of competition in the immediate area... But, having said that, the food and prices here are worth bouncing in for a hot meal if you are visiting Little River Canyon National Park. No need to make the drive into town to eat at a chain restaurant.
The staff is always very nice and you'll get your burger / chicken / BBQ quickly and be back at the Hippie Hole satisfied and full.

resp.text: Thank you for your kind review! We appreciate your business and are glad you stopped in to see us!

name: Dustin Morgan
text: Incredible service!! Friendly staff!! Delicious food!! We stopped in after driving past for lunch and had a great experience!! Here on vacation and would definitely recommend to anyone passing by!!

resp.text: Thank you so much we try hard and truly appreciate all of you guys.

name: Alex Harry
text: This place is great. Amazing food, friendly staff. Wonderful after a day out climbing I  the little river caynon. Would highly recommend 👍

resp.text: Thank you so much Alex for taking the time to leave us a review.  We appreciate your kind word and you business we hope to serve you again soon.

name: SlushyCatDude
text: This place is a very great store. the place has become more and more popular with a new owner. not a fast food place it's a great food place. lately, they have been jam-packed, but they still deliver. all staff are hard working and don't slack off. some people don't understand that their not a fast food place they're a restaurant. they can't make great food fast when understaffed. but if you wait a while talking to the locals or look around the store while they make the food you'll be surprised how great the food is. many people can't wait and that's understandable but don't say that they are a bad store if you don't have the patience to get great food.

resp.text: Thank you for your review and your understanding of our desire to always put out the best food possible.  We appreciate your kind words.

name: Marilyn Custer
text: Coming from Geraldine we were looking for a Mom n’Pop place for breakfast and this is what we found. Don’t be deceived by the store front. The food was good, really good, and the people were so friendly. We were glad to find it and will be back!!

name: Sue In TN
text: I read about this place online, and since we were headed up to the Little River Canyon Preserve, we decided to stop in here for a quick lunch.  Based on the reviews, it sounded wonderful.  I got a cheeseburger combo which was only a little over $6.00 and included my drink.   Wow.... I really think it was the best cheeseburger that I've ever had.... the french fries were those 'crinkle' kind and were so good... not one bit greasy.  Our food was ready very quickly, and everyone there was so nice and friendly.  Don't pay any attention to that poster who only gave it a one star.  It seems as though they were there during the World's Longest Yard Sale which brought so many people to the area, and they must have been swamped.  That is only once per year...... it's not a typical occurrence for them to be slow.  Focus on all the other reviews which are 5 stars.

resp.text: Thank your for your nice review. We appreciate your business!

name: Laura McKenzie
text: The grilled chicken sandwiches were delicious.  Our order was accidentally picked up by another family. The staff quickly cooked, from scratch, a new order and were as kind as could be.  Great place to stop after hiking.

resp.text: We appreciate your kind words and your understanding that accidents happen.  Please come eat with us again soon.

name: Tabitha Kinser
text: Over priced and slow getting out. Food was cold.

name: Carmel McNeese
text: Just ate here, and my husband and I were pleasantly pleased. Friendly staff, big portions, and delicious food! No long wait,  to boot!

resp.text: Thank you for taking the time to let us know how we are doing. We have a great staff who can put out delicious food and we all take great pride in our work. We hope to see you guys again soon.

name: Jason Baldwin
text: Friendly staff unable to put out food.  I arrived at 2 p.m. on Saturday with a big appetite and high hopes after reading G reviews.  I ordered a cheeseburger at the inside window and sat down with my self-serve drink.  It should have been a tip-off that NONE of the other 10-12 seated customers had any food, only drinks.  The eating area was full of flies, and the floors were pretty dirty.  I waited and waited and waited.  After 25 MINUTES OF WAITING, some of the people there before me still did not have any food. so I cancelled my order, paid for my drink, and left.  I know this place has lots of fans, but on this particular Saturday, they seemed incapable of putting out burgers.

resp.text: We appreciate your input and it was unfortunate for you and us that you stopped in at such a busy time of the day.  We do apologize and would like you to know we are not a fast food restaurant.  We make all food to order, meaning no staging of precooked food,  our cooks prep all ingredients fresh daily.  We like to say we are not fast food we do good food fast.  With increased visitation to Little River Canyon we have become well know especially for our burgers.  If you are ever in the area again please give us another visit I promise you we are worth the wait.

name: Suzanne Phillips
text: We had the lunch special and loved it! Highly recommend this place just outside of the Little River Canyon National Preserve. Great friendly service, good prices, and indoor/outdoor dining. Hit the spot!

name: Sharon Williams
text: Love the updates. Staff are so friendly and food is delicious!

resp.text: Thank you Sharon! We are all so excited and proud of all the improvements both inside and out. We have an excellent staff who truly want each customer to have the same experience you did. We appreciate the feed back thanks for your time. We look forward to serving you again soon.

name: Keller Rongey
text: Great food. VERY pleasant staff. Clean and friendly.

name: Michael Culberson
text: We stopped to have lunch after driving around the canyon today. The hamburger was DELICIOUS!!!!! If you’re anywhere near the area, please stop here. The prices were low and the food was great.

resp.text: So glad you stopped in for a quick bite! Thank you for your business!

name: PandaMagicBooty
text: I'm amending my previous review of Ralph's because my most recent trip was fantastic. The wait was short, the food was delicious, and the staff was (and always is) friendly.

resp.text: Thank you for comments and your business.  Our apologizes for the faulty equipment it happens from time to time.  We are implementing new ideas to decrease wait time while serving the same great food. Please visit us again and thank you for your continued support of a family owned business.

name: William Gómez
text: Very delicious food and very friendly staff

resp.text: Thank you William for dining with us.  We are so glad you enjoyed your meal and so appreciate you taking the time to give us a review.  Customers such as you leaving a comment lets us know we are doing our jobs correctly.  It was a pleasure to serve you and hope to see you again soon.

name: jeremy irwin
text: These burgers are sooo good after a long day hiking the beautiful canyon! Made to order, and definitely worth the wait!! Corn nuggets and fried okra on point!

resp.text: The weather was perfect for hiking and we are so happy you finished your day with our burgers and sides! We look forward to seeing you again soon! Thank you for your business!

name: Pam Ogle
text: The BEST cheeseburgers in Fort Payne AL! And let’s not forget the AMAZING 1inch thick, light&fluffy pancakes for breakfast that are as big as the plate!!!! Great service too! Hands down my families FAVORITE restaurant for Breakfast, Lunch and Supper!

resp.text: Thank you so much! We are so glad you enjoy our burgers and pancakes! We appreciate your business and can’t wait to see you again soon!

name: Jeremy Moses
text: A must for a local burger. Great laid back atmosphere with excellent food and friendly service. If you are visiting little river canyon, make the day perfect by stopping at Ralph's.

resp.text: We appreciate your business! Thanks for stopping in!

name: Porkchopranch
text: Real good food no matter what you order. Service is very good and the prices are reasonable. Everything is fresh and served fresh. Great cheeseburgers and plate lunches.

resp.text: We appreciate your kind review. Thank you for your business!

name: Kenneth Blanchard
text: Staff was very nice and fun. I ate the large cheeseburger and it was definitely better than any gourmet burger I've had. I wish I lived closer. If you're on the area definitely stop in to eat. You won t be disappointed.

name: Scott Price
text: Love this place!! Great food and wonderful restaurants in store employees.

resp.text: Thank you Scott for your comment and support. We appreciate you and Susan and look forward to seeing you soon.

name: Clay Massengale
text: Non existent service.  Slow service was fine. I wasn’t in a hurry.  But after a 40 minute wait for a child’s cheeseburger we gave up and left.  Perhaps the four dollars they beat us out of will help them hire better employees.

resp.text: We apologize for the lack of service you experienced during your visit. During a busy weekend, we found ourselves short staffed and hope you will give us another try in the future.

name: Melanie Broome
text: AMAZING hippy burger this place hand makes the epitome of All burgers. yummmmm

resp.text: So glad you had the opportunity to dine with us and being courageous enough to try our Hippy Hole burger considering its size. Thanks so much hope to see you again soon.

name: Jason Druebert
text: Hands down the best burger in Northeast Alabama.

resp.text: Thank you Jason for taking the time to let us know how we are doing. Look forward to seeing you again.

name: Randy Williams
text: Great food always.

resp.text: Thanks Randy hope to serve you again soon.

name: Charles Curio
text:
Other guy was right, it was about 25/30 minutes and I was getting irritated...but the reply was right on..it was busy, but the food (burgers, Patty melt, fries) freaking awesome and worth the wait, hands down.
We'll come and wait, and eat again!

name: Jonathan Vance
text: Best place around!!!!!

resp.text: Thank you Jonathan we are so excited to hear from our customers. Guess it goes without saying especially when we got it exactly right for you. We appreciate your business and hope to serve you soon.

name: Richard Kuhn
text: Great place to grab breakfast, lunch, gas, or convenience items in between your little river canyon adventures. Great burgers. Clean and friendly.

name: Michael Shad
text: Very friendly staff and always good food. Best burgers within 25 miles.

resp.text: We appreciate your kind words! Thank you for your business, and we agree our burgers are the best!

name: Ron G
text: Best burgers on the mountain! Nice Lil quick stop for gas and camping supplies.

name: Lee Battles
text: Food like my Mawmaw used to make. Try it one time and check out the beautiful falls just next door.

resp.text: Within minutes from Little River Canyon and falls, we are glad you came in to visit! Come back and see us soon! Thanks!

name: J J
text: Great stop for great food!

resp.text: Thanks for stopping in! We appreciate your business and look forward to seeing you again soon!

name: Becky Payne
text: On our way to have breakfast here. A favorite place to visit each time we come to Ft. Payne!

resp.text: We appreciate you coming in to have breakfast with us! Thanks for your review!

name: Austin Rampey
text: Great spot.

resp.text: Thanks for coming in to see us! We appreciate your business!

name: Rickey White
text: Best meatloaf

resp.text: Thanks Rickey! We couldn’t agree with you more!!

name: cotton w
text: I will definitely be back

resp.text: Thank you for your business! Check out our daily lunch specials on our Facebook page!

name: Drew Cottrell
text: Very friendly staff and large selection of snacks before you go into little river falls

name: Bella Dennis
text: Good good nice people

resp.text: Thank you for your review! We love our team members too! We appreciate your business and hope to see you again soon!

name: Richard Hartline
text: Cheapest gas prices in Fort Payne.

name: luke lewis
text: DO NOT STOP HERE! Rest room was disgusting, and they charge high rates for products. They charged me over $2 just to put ice in my own water bottle.

name: Steve Spencer
text: Great place to get fuel friendly staff especially teresea she all ways has a smile on and very friendly stop by and tell her hi

name: Tyler Luthy
text: Clerk was sketchy accused me of loading my pockets. Bc I was checking energy drink shots bc half of the ones on the shelf we're 3 months or more expired. So I emptied my pockets on the counter and lifted my shirt as I was upset to be called a thief. And the clerk was like I'm one hell of a fighter let's go outside if you want too.. like what, no I'm here to buy something you jittery POS. Then he tried to charge me triple for the product. He was pathetic!

name: Kasey McKay
text: The website says its open.......it is NOT open during the hours it states it is, so if you are on the phone with your child who is low on gas and try to help them find a gas station just ignore this one.....because it might not be open.

name: John Smith
text: High quality gas, if I do say so myself.

name: Bobby Brown
text: Now I remember why I do not buy cigarettes from Mapco. The price is always wrong ex. The sign said $4.49 but the price is $4.96 and it said buy 2 save $0.50 but that is not true either. What else are they cheating us on?

name: Grant Dalton
text: Broken seal, this speaks for itself.

name: Nick Burgess
text: Mapco is a great place to come & get gas, get food w/ Mapco rewards u can't go wrong!!

name: Andy King
text: Hounded for money 4 times in 10 minutes. Saw them scare a young woman.

name: Dee Bail
text: Clean store, nice facility.

name: gerald Howard
text: The cashiers at this Mapco were the rudest and most unprofessional I have ever seen! Every single time I visit! Especially, the tall lady. She acts as if you're borrowing gas and not paying for it. Mapco Publix and Chick-fil-A are known for their courteous employees, but this location is tearing your name down!

resp.text: We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you that behavior goes against our culture standards. We have alerted the District Manager over that location to take swift action.

name: Charity Shackelford
text: I would like to take this time to share a wonderful experience at this location. I purchased product at this particular location tonight. After my purchase I got in my car and was pulling out of the lot when a wonderful man by the name of Aaron came running to my car with my phone I had left on the counter. Thank you so very much for having such an honest and caring person on your team. Aaron you have no idea how much that meant. You saved so many photos/video's, all memories that I could never get back if it hadn't been for you. THANK YOU!

resp.text: Thank you for leaving such a nice review. We are glad that you loved our services, our dedicated staff will be pleased to learn of your high praise.

name: Mikie Morris (Mikie)
text: It was a few yrs ago that I had visited this establishment and being that Im from Colorado I was happy to find a fuel station in the area that sold diesel fuel. The cashier that night was more than helpful in answering a couple of questions for me. So I can't say anything bad about this place it was definitely a brighter note in my horrendous trip to the Huntsville area.

resp.text: Mikie, We are happy to hear you had a positive experience at MAPCO! We value your input and encourage you to let us know more details about your experience with us.

name: Debra Tarbox
text: Never have problems except when I come when it's busy. The staff are polite and that's even after dealing with disagreeable people. No matter where you go there are idiot drivers and people who think everyone owes them. Bless the staff who endure this corner of this side of town.

resp.text: Debra, Thank you again and it really helps to have customers like you sharing feedback regarding our performance.

name: Tiffany Wallace
text: The door was wide open when I went inside the store last night to buy drinks. I sat at the register for about 5 minutes with no one at the desk or even in the store. The lady behind me went out to the patio to find a cashier, and one came back in only to tell us they were closed. It was close to 4 AM, yet they say they're open for 24 hours.... Needless to say, I left the drinks I was planning to buy at the register and walked out. I'm not happy with their service at all.

resp.text:
Tiffany, We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you that we have alerted the team of operations over that location to take swift action and resolve this matter.
Please allow us to earn back your trust.

name: Reese B
text: Don’t go here if you expect to do a quick stop. They usually have about 10 employees mingling around with one person takin cash. God bless you if they start chatting with the cashier because that’s going to tack on another 10 minutes to your trip

name: Jessie Basinger
text: Door was not set on automatic it was opened up 2". When we watched a local cop open the door by hand and go into the bathroom we followed. They told us...paying customers in uniform also (emergency road service crew) that only cops are allowed in right now... I suggest EVERYONE GO ACROSS THE STREET TO SUNOCO!! Very nice staff and actually open 24 hrs.

name: Daniel Yearta
text: I try to make sure I spend the least amount of my time & money here, as possible. It's one of those places that just want to appear to be clean on the outside but on the inside it's kinda disgusting. Workers attitudes toward customers are based on the color of your skin, normally only one cashier during busiest times of day, bathrooms are always atrocious and/or missing toilet paper/hand towels/soap, and most food is over or under cooked, if it's not already pre packaged and over priced. I only stop here if it's all that's open, if it's actually open, and in case of extreme emergencies. I avoid it like the plague! Enter at your own risk.

name: Victor Brant
text: 6:35am on 5/22/19 - Come in - Jessica says "HI". Get my coffee and start to head up to register. Again the store manager(tall black man) is behind the register. Jessica is at a register that has about 10+ customers in line. He calls for the next person in line. This goes on for a couple of minutes. I am next inline to be called "next", he looks up and see's who I am and he walks off!! With more than 10+ customers still in line to be helped! The customer in front of me finishes and Jessica greats me with a smile. "Good morning, did you see that", I asked Jessica. "Yes I did", she replied. This is the 3rd time this employee has provided very poor customer service, almost to the point that I am taking offence to it. I am thinking that Mapco is not going to do anything about it since nothing has happened.  It is a real shame that 1 employee can ruin your whole day and make your stores attitude not very pleasant to visit or deal with. I hope that you will take ahold of this comment and actually do something about it.

resp.text:
Victor, We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you that behavior goes against our culture standards. We have alerted the District Manager over that location to take swift action and resolve this issue.
Please allow us to earn back your trust.

name: kitt Tidwell
text: Was about to make a $30 dollar purchase but was trying to find saltine crackers. My black boyfriend who was carrying the charcoal we were going to buy got approached by the cashier even though she had 5 people still in her line. She told him we were taking too long and needed to hurry up pay and leave. He went to the line after I gave up on my crackers and I went ahead to the side and asked her what the issue was. She just glared at me and wouldn't answer. I requested her the number of the manager, she gave me a fake number I found out later, and then told me I needed to leave or she would call the cops. My boyfriend and I deal with people against interracial couples all the time but this was absolutely disgusting to be treated this badly.

resp.text: Kit, We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you that behavior goes against our culture standards. We have alerted the District Manager over that location to take swift action and resolve this problem.

name: Amanda Lynn
text: I'm not sure why everyone is giving such poor reviews. My husband and I happened to love this store. The staff and COFFEE are amazing. I'm horrible with names but the lady with red hair is a delight. There is long lines and most of the time there is no creamer in the machine and the coffee bar is dosgusting. But if people would clean up after themselves and do a little self help at the coffee bar, it would go a long ways ! You see the ladies checking all the customers out. We don't go anywhere else for gas or cigarettes.

resp.text: Amanda, Thank you so much for your review!

name: David Rieger
text: This store rarly ever has coffee  made at 1:30 a.m. I generallt gwve ro go to another store revery day for my coffee

resp.text:
David,  We have alerted the upper management  over that location so that they may resolve this issue.
Please allow us to earn back your trust.

name: J Allen
text: The coffee is #1 and the selection is GREAT! They're always busy and lines can get long but they make it up by the quickness and efficientcy of the employees, 2 - 3 minute wait tops!

resp.text: J, Thank you so much for your review!

name: Leah Heatherly
text: I am currently here at 3am this is a 24 hr store..... doors are wide open, and yet you come in just to get told they are closed. Sounds like ur paying your workers to do nothing!!!!! If ur not 24 hrs don’t advertise it

resp.text: Leah, We do apologize for the experience you have described. We can assure you we have notified the  team of operations regarding this situation to ensure this matter will be resolved.

name: Michael Odom
text: 99% of the time the parking lot is full of people loitering and panhandling. The restrooms are always a mess, full of flies, and understocked. There ALWAYS a line at the register, either because they're slow or too busy chatting with their friends.

resp.text: Michael, We apologize for the experience you have described. We do hope that you continue to be our guest at MAPCO and allow us to make your next visit a better experience.

name: J Goodwin
text: Went in to get coffee, a bite, & smokes but instead of getting served was told they was closed & wouldn't be open for another 30 mins when the sign on the door states plainly that they was open, some guy that doesn't even work there is the one whom relayed the message while the employee at the counter didn't even check up, I asked why the sign says 24 hours & his reply is that I could get gas at the pump with a card, there's a lot of gas stations that you can get gas at the pump after hours & they don't have a sign that says they're open for 24 hours cause that wouldn't be the truth, so why are y'all any different? I went to a different Mapco, they was open, & it wasn't 30 mins later. Your online hours also state that y'all are open 24 hrs, so I wasted gas, my time, & was lied to! If you look up Chevron that isn't 24hrs but can still get gas 24hrs hours with a card at the pump their store hours are correct, y'all should change your sign at the door & online to the correct service you provide.

resp.text: We apologize for the experience you described. We can assure you that behavior goes against our culture standards. We have alerted the Operational Leader over that location to take swift action.

name: Jeremy West
text: Consistent Mapco

resp.text: Thanks for placing your trust in us and your willingness to share. We always appreciate hearing back from our guest.

name: Terry Walker
text: I've just returned from this store. The syrup was out on the Coke fountain dispenser so I was only getting the carbonated water. A young man, his first day, understood the problem and relayed the message to another worker. I understand busy days, busy times, so I pulled out a chair and waiting. If ANYONE had acknowledged me at all - "sorry, ma'am, we haven't forgotten you" - but the other two employees wouldn't make eye contact with me at all. I'd be sitting there still waiting if they would've just acknowledged me. I hope a manager will review with them some proper customer service techniques. T

name: Taylor H
text: The worst gas station in the history of gas stations! Most pumps are out of order, card readers don't work, and employees are garbage.

resp.text: Taylor, We apologize for the experience you described and we can assure you this information will be passed on to  operations  over that location to take swift action and resolve this matter.

name: Rebecca Buckner
text: Ling waits inside for customers paying cash means credit / debit customers can't find an open pump while empty vehicles await their owner's return. Frustrating when you just want to get fuel and go.

name: draydre mccoy
text: My experience on 10/23/18... name: Kayla S
text: Easily the worst Mapco in Huntsville. Consistently understaffed with employees that have little to no understanding of customer service or money handling. This store is a black mark on Marco's brand. Its so bad even our law enforcement have stopped making this a rest stop. You will be here for 20 minutes if you need ANYTHING from a cashier. And if they run out of any change at all before you check out, they will take 10 minutes to restock their drawer instead of continuing to take customers and getting change as needed. Most employees will not ID for cigarettes until a manager is present. I don't think any of them have completed high school. All of them are rude as hell too. This is the 4th day in a row I have stopped at this gas station due to work, and all 4 times it has cost me a lot of time. Go to any other Mapco but avoid this one at all costs.

text:
I have contacted the manager to tell her the problems with this store and they said give me a chance to fix the problems..... Well here i sit at 4:50 am again waiting to get in the store. Website says "Open 24 hours, and they tell me that they closed between 4 and 4:20... Hummm Now why did i rush to get here before 4?
Now usually i leave and go to the Mapco on 72 which may I add that store is awsome. People is nice, store clean, coffee made and they update around 1 in the morning.
I sit here watching customer after customer pull up and pull away mad. 😠..... Even our officers that protect this store and is called out over and over to this store...
I totally get they gave to upload there system but they should All do it at the same time every day. And change there website.
May I add that this morning i helped this little lady that needed gas to get to the hospital because her husband was being transported by ambulance all she had was cash she was in 😢 tears.. I used my mapco card with my pay pal and got her gas...
Come inn set a certain time around 2 in the morning when you are less busy.... I would think that 4 to 7 in the morning would be a busy part of your day.....

text: I really like the people who work here. And every morning they have the SmokeHouse guy there with some of the best barbecue. I've seen a couple reveiws and those geniuses  nearly paid double for gas. That's because you picked a fuel with no ethanol.  All you have to do is read the posted sign and it explains everything.  It reads for "regular unleaded" with"ethanol"choose the black handled pump. Or choose the one that's not $3.99 a gallon. 10% ethanol is what most other gas station sell in Montgomery Alabama, with no other options. However, if you happen to choose the green handle at this liberty it is quite a large price difference between $2.59 for E/89 and $3.99 NoE 93. You will see a lot of Motorcycles and big boats being towed to fill up with ethanol free fuel.  It's easy to say somebody else sucks when in reality the blame is yours lol.

name: Barb Knick
text: In short Mike Peebles and his manager, Bob  are true examples of southern hospitality.  Not to mention the wonderful mechanic, Gary Brown, that came to Cowboys to our breakdown rescue!  And alhough Mike had already offered us his parking lot to stay overnight; Gary had us up and running in a mere 2 hours and we were back on the road to the races. The man even refused to take a tip from us.  True gerntlemen and will always remember these true friends in Alabama!!

name: robb reeser
text:
We were traveling from illinois to the race in Talladega and the other motorhome in our group started having problems so they limped into Cowboys! The owner took it upon his self to actually call a mechanic friend of his at 430 in the afternoon "gary the mechanic" showed up and after some diagnosing decided it need an alternator so right there in the parking lot he took the old one iff and went to the parts store. Came back put the new one on in the parking lot of Cowboys and we continued our trip to the race. Mike the owner of Cowboys and his mechanic friend Gary Brown with their "southern hospitality" went above and beyond what most everyday people would have done for us esp in the late afternoon. He even offered for us in both motorhomes to stay the night"free" on his lot . We are so grateful for the 2 of you. Thank your for your kindness and hospitality! I would highly recommendthis station to anyone!

Robb Reeser

text:
First off the guy sounded like he knew what he was doing so I gave him a chance on rebuilding my rearend. He told me that he can do it that all I needed to do is ordered the parts. So I did. So I called made an appointment to bring the truck down. Took it down on Thursday by Friday even it was done so I go pick it up. Everything seemed great going home then the following Sunday going to storage unit an all at once it felt like the brakes was grabbing and released but than I was hearing a noise. It happen so fast I made it to the road to pull off and got out to look. That's when I saw the rearend streaming hot. So I got someone to come get it to take it back. So I hauled it down and called the next day to let him know what happen. Had lots of people thats worked on them. Little farther away. They asked me what it done when it happen and they asked me how many pinion threads was showing so I counted and they was probably an 3/4 of an inch showing so they said that he over tightened it. Well the guy at South auto told me that it was a bad bearing in the kit that it would cost me another 200 or so dollars to be fixed so I've done been tho two different people rebuilding it. Put over $1000 in it already so therefore he wasn't holding his word either. So I just picked my truck up and told him I'll look at it myself bc I don't think it's much I hope. Well come to find out on my carrier bearings are hammer marks instand of pressing them on he used a hammer and beat them in so now Ive gotta put another set of bearing all the way tho the hole rearend. Costing another 100 dollars and free labor bc I'm doing it myself. Taking it apart and looking at it the outer pinion bearings is gone but worth me not driving it far I'm praying that I can clean everything up bc I'm not seeing alot of metal in it so hopefully it will be good after I get it fixed. JUST CANT TRUST ANYONE ON THEIR WORDS. Height not recommend anyone with rearend problems.

IF COULD POST PICS I WOULD OF THE MARKS.

CALLED AND NO ANSWERS SO HE MOST KNOW ITS ME CALLING.

As far as interior gifts items to buy excetera this gas station had more than enough and we did not have problem buying snacks water and using the restroom. Definitely go in and out if possible and hopefully come out safe. Godspeed gents.

On the plus side if you happen to get hungry there is a Little Caesars attached on the left side. I don't know if they have corresponding hours but during normal hours "Pizza Pizza"

I would highly recommend Woodhams Full Service... and plan on stopping in the next time I am in Auburn to introduce myself and thank him personally!

name: David Sims
text:
Was here on 8-12-16. Celeste took my order for a pizza at 4:41. I took a seat in a booth. Celeste apologized for the wait at 4:57. I said no big deal because I know that's not a long wait. However, at 5:11 I said ok guys it's been thirty minutes. How the pizza coming along? Celeste said its coming out now. I walked over to Bonnie and told her what pizza I was picking up and she was confused. Said she could make it. So after waiting thirty minutes my pizza hasn't even been prepped to go into the oven. I asked Celeste how to get in touch with the owner and she said she's new and doesn't even know the owner. Bonnie is just flat out lost. A woman named Margaret was there and showed no interest at all for my situation.
Here's why I'm so pissed. I'm a trucker and had started my ten hour break so I could leave at 2:30 the next morning. To get food, I had to restart my clock and drive to the next truckstop. I had problem with Bonnie last time I was there about six months ago because she skipped taking my food order to ring up items of people she knows. And I reminded her of that today. These three could screw up a two car funeral. No way if I owned this place would I leave it with these people!!!!!

Just saying

resp.text: Hi Dahl, Thanks for stopping and for your comment.  It helps to know how we are doing and what we need to improve on.  Your right, We can be short handed at lunch times due to the fact that some days we don't have a lunch rush and sometimes we do, so that makes it hard to schedule an extra person for economic reasons.  I am so glad to hear at least that the food was good to you.  Unfortunately, if it seemed like we didn't care, WE DO, we are just usually busy doing what we can to make things go fast as they can.  Hope you can try us again or at least at another time when we are not in a lunch rush!  Thanks for your business, WE DO APPRECIATE IT!

text: They took advantage of my teenage son.  The pump handle stuck and wouldn't stop after the tank filled.  He ran to get them to shut off the pump after getting gas all over his clothes. When I returned an hour later to ask for a refund, all of the pumps were shut off, as shown in the pictures, because they had another problem.  They refused a refund, refused to look at video to show that my car savvy son did nothing that could cause this problem, and forwarded my info to another manager.  Bottom line:  the gas price may be cheap but they are crooked, disrespectful, and refuse to admit the pumps are broken.  I'm looking forward to the opening of a Kroger gas station just down 72.

The girls have been very polite up until recently and not quite sure why that's changed but it's made me feel unwelcomed and I guess I'll have to start going back to Jack's. The older ladies are always nice and polite and though I could understand if it was sporadic visits during the week but it's literally everyday that I come for breakfast and lunch. They have great coffee the best I've found in Cullman. Again though the attitudes have made my visits undesirable and I'll be going there less now.  Another example has been when I get wings or chicken strips or even a hamburger they dont ask if I want condiments that generally go with the food but they will ask everyone around me if they want sauce or lettuce and tomato??? I am in Cullman for work purposes and when I found this place it was like a little hole from home and I fell in love but that has since deteriorated a bit and will be visiting less. :(

Also maybe add more variety of lunch menu items. I walked in as a brand New customer over a month ago, The assistant manager was lovely and ordered my brand of cigarettes, she kept them in stock.

I agreed to buy multiple cartons per week. I bought a lot!  The manager just told me (today), she will not order anymore new cigarettes until the 4 cartons of two-year-old  cigarettes in the back are sold.  The cigarette supplier told her that cigarettes last for five years . The manufacturer of  my brand says they stay fresh for one year .  Any smoker will tell you they go stale after one year!

Your manager and supplier lost you a good customer.  I will take my business elsewhere .  I would recommend making the assistant manager the main manager , she’s the one who will grow your  Business and work to retain and keep customers who spend money!

Bye Exon!

You had more than one customer try to open the door and proceeded to shut the lights out. ALL OF THEM. INSIDE AND OUT! With people standing at the door! I understand having closing work to do but that was BEYOND rude. I called your store. You answered "Marathon" and when asked why you closed an hour early your reply was "honey, this is a residence. They don't have a phone there anymore. Sorry." And then you hung up on me. I don't appreciate being hung up on for one and for two, don't call me honey. I will find a way to contact a manager tomorrow if I have to start at cooperate and work my way down. I hope you sleep well tonight knowing you left people standing in the pitch black DARK. I will be absolutely sure to let every single person I know (which is QUITE a many) to keep driving up the road to the Shell where you aren't treated like a nuisance.

DO NOT SHOP HERE! I walked in with a mask to protect myself and others in the store, the store attendant was rude and demanded I take off my
mask or I wouldn’t be provided service. I thought she was joking until another customer walked in with a mask and she demanded him to remove his mask. I said to the attendant, I refuse to remove my mask, you can believe what you want; but I need to ensure you are not infected with the virus and the only way to do that, is to wear a mask.
She began to yell stating she didn’t believe the covid hype.
Me- that’s your choice, but you have no business to tell me or anyone else not to wear one, if we chose to protect ourselves. If you want covid that’s your business and choice but I will not remove my mask. She started to yell even louder how I need to remove my mask and how she’ll call the cops for me wearing one. I’ll tell them you tried to rob me, then you’ll take your mask off. I replied to call them. I laughed of course. She continued to yell, degrading me. I told her  her behavior is not needed,  I will take my Business elsewhere! You mad over a mask for what.. 😂🤣😂
No wonder why Alabama covid cases are on the rise, too many people without common sense.

Happened- July 5, 2020 @8:00AM!

name: Charlie Warren
text:
Paresh Mistry, (Pronounced "Parish Mystery") & Hemant, (Pronounced "Hammond") & Hemant's Wife Puru, (Pronouced "Peru"), are so Cordial that it is Always a Pleasure going inside to Chat with them... Even if I Am just going to Pay at the Pump Outside, I Go Inside Just to Talk With them.  This is a Value Added Stop~!

And talk about Upscale, the Restrooms with Lights that come on Automatically when you walk in and Marble Tiled Walls Rival the Best Hotels in the World~!  You must stop here, if for nothing else just to see the bathrooms. The Restrooms Certainly Smell Fresh And Just like the Kind Folks at the Front that are Always Smiling, this is a very Pleasant Stop and will add Joy to your Step and a Sparkle in your Eye, (plus, They are the only Convenient Store for miles around that sale Zagnut Candy Bars).

Even if I am 30-40 miles away and Low on Gas, but I can make it back to Papa John's that's what I do ~ because I so Enjoy the Friendly Atmosphere that doesn't Vex me.  With the LED Track Lighting, the Store is Always Bright and Cheery.

And they also sell the Hard to Find Non-Ethanol Gasoline.  From my Experience, You can be sure that you'll Always get Exceptionally Great Gasoline here that won't make your Vehicle Gurgle, and that there won't be any water in their Tank.  And all their Pumps are brand-new with Video Displays on them.

Ask them about the Warren Fire Starter Fluid, (No Relationship), and they'll know I sent you~!

name: Step East
text: The cashier who assisted me had zero people skills! I bought $10 worth of gas, a Smart Water and the last four bananas they had for sale at 2 for $1.00, yet I was charged $1.00 PER banana, doubling their price. When I brought this to her attention, she reiterated my point and agreed that the price of bananas was, in fact, 2 for $1.00 - not 1 for $1.00, which is outrageously high, however, even though she rang my order up incorrectly, and even though I paid with cash, making it the most uncomplicated type of transaction possible, she still refused to reimburse me for the difference and she even told me that if I wanted a refund I'd have to come back the following day to see a manager. She had a very condescending tone and demeanor; she even had the audacity to catch an attitude with me as if it were she who'd been overcharged and inconvenienced. Until Circle K can hire and train clerks with customer service skills, I'll take my business across the street to Texaco.

name: grace skidmore
text:
Their motto is to treat you like family and they do! professional, friendly caring and kind this team exhibits performance excellence. They are expeditious and knowledgeable plus willing to go the extra mile to get the job done. When they have to deliver less than desired news they are forthright and honest. The integrity of this outfit is refreshing to find and is a credit to the long history and tradition of being customer-centric.

John and his crew will take care of you and your auto repairs. No need to go anywhere else.

name: Ashraf Hijaz
text: Best customer service in town, no Ethanol in their fuel.

name: Jose Vazquez
text: Personable and kind staff. My car battery died and they had someone come tow my car right away. The mechanic got to it really quick and my vehicle was ready for pick up the same day. The mechanic took his time to explain other issues he saw and was able to address — he even called ahead and asked if I wanted my oil changed. Highly recommend bringing your car here. Just call ahead and ask if it’s busy since the shop is pretty small compared to others.

name: Charlie Pennell
text: Cloverdale Service Center is my go to place for all work needed on my car. Great service and always professional. Anyone needing any work done on their vehicles check out Cloverdale Service Center.  John and his team always treat me like family.

name: Penny Weaver
text: There's lots to like about Montgomery's Cloverdale neighborhood, and at the top of that list is Cloverdale Service Center. Not only is it a convenient stop for high-quality gas, John and his skilled staff provide prompt, dependable service on most anything your car may need. Need a set of tires? John can suggest the best choice for your vehicle, order and install them with no hassle for you. We dropped our car off at closing time on Monday, and it was ready to go, new tires in place and aligned, before 11 the next morning. It is a comfort to have a reliable resource like Cloverdale Service Center nearby.

name: Amanda Giddings
text: I got stuck in Montgomery on my way home from Pensacola and was fortunate enough to find this amazing auto shop. They managed to fix my car despite it being hard to find parts near them and got me back on the road within a day. With me being a college student traveling alone and getting stuck somewhere I’ve never been, I was beyond grateful to have found this place. They showed me the problems with my car that led to it breaking down and told me exactly how they intended to fix it as well as how much it would cost. The people there were also very kind and accommodating. If I lived in the area, this would be my go to auto shop and I certainly intend to go there again if I ever find myself in the area. I recommend this without question for anyone seeking auto services in this area.

text: Honest work and fair prices.  I paid $100 to the Toyota dealership mechanics to plug in the computer and tell me nothing was wrong with my car - I doubt they even lifted the hood, let alone test drove it!  John at Cloverdale Service inspected and replaced burned out spark plugs and corroded battery wire - something the previous mechanics should have easily diagnosed if they'd bothered to look past the computer screen!  Got everything fixed up, plus oil change, for an extremely reasonable price, and now my 13 year old car runs like new!  This is my go-to mechanic from now on!

text:
New to the area and didn't know anyone who could suggest somewhere to get my car worked on who I could trust. Looked online and saw "family environment", "great people", "great service" frequently associated with Cloverdale. Those reviews were nothing short of the truth. All of the staff was extremely friendly, helpful and genuinely cared not only about getting me in and out, but made a lasting impression on me personally.

I only had minor service done, but my time was not wasted ...like you normally feel when you sit at a car shop for hours just to get an oil change. I was in and out in less than 30 minutes!

I would suggest Cloverdale to any and everyone I know.
