text: I went to buy two drinks, a good living cola fizz and a naked green machine, the naked smoothie had a $1.99 under both flavors. At the register the new employee, Tammy, said the smoothie was $3.49 I told her it's priced here at $1.99. She went to the food deli and got this blonde who came with me so I could show her. She pointed to the drink on the other side of the shelf, so I asked then why is the $1.99 straight under the naked smoothies. She goes around to the back of the shelf when she comes out her exact words were "they are just misshelfed." I asked "since they are the price advertised that's what I'm getting it for right." She procced to tell me "no I'm not but we have cheaper drinks if you can't afford it." On top of all that she said it in front of four customers, which one female customer who was buying the same drink said I'll just go to pilot across street where they dont mistreat they're customers. So I bought the cola fizz and ask the cashier who told me her name was Tammy. Then I ask Tammy how to contact the manager she looked behind her at the blonde from the food area who shook her head no and Tammy said she couldn't give that information out so I ask what the blonde employees name was and she tried to say she didn't know it. After one or two other customers put their things down and left the store saying they wouldn't ever be back as will I unless the nameless blonde does not work there at all, for her very rude and unprofessional behavior. I would still like to talk to her manager because I've never been so humiliated in my life. Please fix this horrible employee with the attitude problem. False advertisements can be pretty harsh in the state of Alabama.

text: Thank you so much to Linnsey & Chris! We called roadside assistance with our insurance company and they couldn't find a wrecker service. But the wonderful people of Birmingham Police gave us the number for Weil Wrecker who directed us to M & M! Thank you all for your fantastic help in our time of need!

name: Fridgemate Clips
text: We we down at 7pm on a Sunday and had a tech with us at 7:30 and back on the road by 8:15. Very friendly, helpful and reasonably priced for emergency after hours help.  Technician was professional and fast.  Our thanks for the assist!

name: Dr. Matt and Debra St. John
text: We ran out of fuel about 1/8th of a mile from this business in our minivan and called this place to see if they could help us out by running over a gallon of fuel and us pay them for it.  The lady on the phone informed me that they would charge a $105 service fee, the cost of fuel, and for two hours of labor.  The total was around $350.  I am not joking.  I politely got off the phone with her, called Warrior Tractor, and within 10 minutes we had a truck with two guys pouring 5 gallons of fuel in.  They refused any payment.  Because they aren't greedy scum like M&M.

name: Katrina Dominey
text: We would like to thank y'all again for your service. Your tech who's name we didn't get was absolutely amazing. Fast and efficient. Even after waking him up to come fix our tire he was still unbelievably pleasant. Carla the night dispatcher was so sweet and so helpful. I will be recommending M&M to anyone and everyone. Thanks again for your outstanding service and hospitality.

name: Cristina Clemens
text:
The young lady that works from 6am - 1pm is very helpful and courteous! Very polite and respectful.

Now the gentleman that works the evening shift, who happens to conveniently own the store, is very rude, disrespectful, and does not accept ALL American currency. Let me explain, I went to this gas station on a Thursday afternoon around 3pm about a month ago. It was the day before payday, and had only 4 dollar bills and a little over $2 in loose change. Got which item/s I needed and went to pay and he refused to let me purchase the item/s because I had $1.21 in pennies. I argued with him for a couple minutes and finally gave up and grabbed my money off the counter and as I was walking out, I reminded this man that pennies are an American currency too, and walked out. I get into the vehicle and I hear this man yelling at me saying this is his country and to be honest I couldn't make out what he was saying after that. This man pursued me and chased me out to my car and was pretty much threatening me. A week later, I returned to the store with my boyfriend, but this time I did not go in the store. This man informed my boyfriend that if i come back to the store he will call the police and have me arrested! What kind of BS is that?? Do not suggest going to this store EVER!!

name: Orlando Crawford
text:
Up to the other day I was a faithful customer. I Love the dark roasted coffee. I go there every morning & on both of my off days. Service is friendly. I get a large coffee & reuse the cup the next morning so I can get it  @ $.99. Instead of the $1.07. The special is refills are just $.99. There cup or your own. I haven't missed a day in six month. Just ask my wife. I always give the $.03 to the charity or just say to the cashier to keep it tell I'm in a bind or the next person needs it.  For Trusting right. Well on the morning I only had exactly $.97 cents but no cup. I got told I would be charged $1.07. Ok, I come s7 days a week, I buy gas twice a month, I fuel up, $35- 45 dollars biweekly. I have two car so I fuel them both. For $.08 cents you would lose a good customer. That spends over $250.00+ a month. You do the math. Yea your sales are good, you are one of the busiest store in Huntsville, and your coffee sale drive your business. But you lost a good and faithful customer this week. Sad I can't get my favorite coffee any longer from you but in the long run you will loss more. Sorry & I'll keep my &.08 cents and donate it to a worthy charity.
Best wishes

name: Brian East
text: The staff in this place around 10:15 p.m. on Wednesday 11.1.17 were ghetto an incompetent. I don't live in Huntsville and never come to this side of town, but tonight I gave a coworker a ride home and decided to stop by and get gas and a can of chewing tobacco.  My coworker offered to go in and pay for the gas so I asked him to grab a can of dip.  He came back out and I realized they gave him the wrong can. He went back in and asked them to switch it , and they wouldn't. I decided I would go in and politely ask them to make it right, as I walked in the cashier and a group of black girls were looking at me and saying " Y'all don't go nowhere white boy mad , they gone be blood ". I politely asked the other cashier to switch my dip and he explained that the "laws for Mapco " stated that he could not exchange it once it left the door. I just politely asked if Mapco laws were different than those in the rest of Alabama. Once I realized he was not going to make it right I left the can on the counter and told them to keep it. I'm sure they pocketed my $3. People like the employees I encountered tonight are the ones that give certain parts of Huntsville a bad name. I won't be back. ~Brian from Athens.

resp.text:
Brian I assure you this is not the MAPCO culture and will be addressed. I would like to speak with you further about this incident. Can you please email me your contact information? guestexperience@mapcoexpress.com
Thank you - Toni MAPCO Guest Experience Manager.

name: Emmitt Bishop (barbaroi52)
text: I bought a can of fix a flat from this place and found out the top was broken when I tried to use it. I handed it to the clerk and proceeded to pick up another can of a different brand. Because it seemed to be higher quality I walked to the counter to pay the difference. The clerk then informs me that he knows that I broke the top. That was news to me considering that it was broken when I opened it. He proceeds to tell me he doesn't trust me and gets offended that I'm taking issue with being accused and insulted over a $4.00 can of fix a damned flat. Because I had no time or patience for this nonsense I paid full price for the second can and walked away in complete disbelief of the audacity of this exceptional human being. Why on earth would inspire distrust over 4.00 insignificant dollars that I paid with my bloody Platinum Business American Express card? People worried about 4 damned dollars rarely even see one of those. Oh I forgot I'm black. Silly me.

name: leplane
text:
Went there with an emergency situation. Asked if they could patch a leaking gas tank that was dropping gas on the exhaust pipe! (they are a shop repair as well as a gas station -).

The manager didn't even bother to look at where the leak was coming from (even though I told him where it was) and suggested a gas tank replacement instead.

When I asked him if he would at least patch it so I could drive it home, he gave me excuses as to why it can't be done and kept suggesting the gas tank replacement ignoring my requests. Shops do fix small gas tank leaks, but he wanted $$$.

They were kind tho, I give them props on that, but not helpful at all. This is not how you treat customers. I will not return or use their gas station at all.

name: C R
text: We are on MANDATORY FACE MASK USE and 50% of the people had no face mask even though there is a sign on the door. The employees have been told that refusing anyone service at this location will cost them their employment. I will be giving the health department and the Governors office a call. The Government MANDATED this and no one's employment should be threatened. The longer we continue to ignore this mandate the longer we are going to continue to battle this virus and continue deplete the economy due to the inability for employees to return to work.

resp.text:
Hi C R,
With safety as our highest priority, BP is closely monitoring the spread of the illness caused by COVID-19. Many of our retail sites are independently owned and operated, and we have recommended that station owners take actions to prevent spreading, including placing hand sanitizers at registers and disinfecting frequently touched objects and surfaces such as pin pads and nozzles. We have contacted the station owner to remind them of the need to follow local and state requirements.
Thanks,
BP

name: Dennis Baribeau
text: I go to this gas station everyday. They keep beer/fountain drinks/cigarettes well stocked, but beware if you're buying sandwiches/burritos from the cooler in the middle of the store. They're not dated like they're supposed to be & on 2 separate occasions I've bought a sandwich or burrito there & it was completely moldy. They need to enforce FIFO with their inventory & properly date products. I'm just lucky enough to have checked under the bun before eating it.  Otherwise it's a gas station with good service.

name: Angie Dunham
text: I originally posted my review a little over a year ago. I felt the need to update it due to recent travels. This location is one of my top 2 favorites! Everyone is always very friendly and welcoming! I stop here a couple of times a day 7 days a week (unless I'm out of town) for crushed ice and whatever else I need at the time. I'm always met with a smile and personal greeting. I will continue to be a loyal customer! They also have the best bathrooms and gas prices!
